      "microtonal_inflections": "Gamelan tuning varies from ensemble to ensemble with deliberate mistuning (beating) between paired instruments creating the characteristic shimmer. These are not 'standardized' but are essential aesthetic elements.",
      "rhythmic_features": "Organized through cyclic structures called gongan, with instruments marking specific points in the cycle. Dense interlocking patterns (kotekan) feature prominently in performance practice.",
      "ornamentation": "Melodic ornamentation (cengkok) involves specific patterns for each instrument, with lead instruments (rebab, gender) guiding the ensemble through elaborate ornamental passages.",
      "instrumentation": "Bronze metallophones, gongs, drums, and occasional strings and vocals form the traditional gamelan ensemble, with instruments grouped in families tuned to specific registers."
